M|Comm|tx|\| Mistake \| Why It Hurts \| Fix \|
M|Comm|tx|\|---------\|-------------\|-----\|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Too many metrics (>15)** \| Information overload, no focus \| Cut to the vital few that indicate health \|
M|Comm|| **|activities and inputs \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **No owner assigned** \| "Someone will handle it" means nobody does \| One name per metric, no exceptions \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Goals too easy** \| Scorecard is always green, masks problems \| Set goals that require effort but are achievable \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Goals too hard** \| Scorecard is always red, creates learned helplessness \| Base goals on 13-week average plus realistic stretch \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Not reviewed weekly** \| Data goes stale, accountability disappears \| Scorecard is agenda item #2 in every Level 10 meeting \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Monthly instead of weekly** \| Lose 4 weeks of correction time \| Convert monthly metrics to weekly proxies \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Vanity metrics** \| Numbers that look good but do not drive the business \| Replace w/ metrics tied to rv or cs outcomes \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **No trending view** \| See this week but miss the pattern \| Always show 13 trailing weeks \|
M|Comm|tx|\| **Changing metrics too often** \| No baseline for comparison \| Lock metrics for at least one full quarter \|
M|When|**Ac|
M|When|it|You need early wn signals
M|When|it|You want to influence behavior
M|When|it|The sales cycle is long (weeks or months)
M|When|it|You are building new processes
M|When|**Re|
M|When|it|You need to confirm the activities are producing outcomes
M|When|it|You are reporting to a board or investors
M|When|it|The metric is a business health vital sign (cash, churn, rv)
M|Bala|tx|```
M|Bala|tx|LEADING (Activities)          LAGGING (Results)
M|Bala|tx|├── Calls made                ├── rv
M|Bala|tx|├── Demos given               ├── Profit margin
M|Bala|tx|├── Proposals sent            ├── cs churn
