M|Bala|tx|└── Tickets resolved
M|Bala|tx|```
M|Bala|tx|A healthy Scorecard has both tp in roughly a 70/30 split favoring leading indicators.
M|How |The |
M|Scor|tx|1. **Display the Scorecard** so all attendees can see it (projector, shared screen, or printed)
M|Scor|tx|2. **Go metric by metric.** The owner reads the number and states "on track" or "off track."
M|Scor|tx|3. **No discussion during rv.** If a number is off track, the owner simply states the number and says "dropping to Issues List."
M|Scor|4. *|5 minutes.** This is a quick scan, not a deep dive. Deep dives happen during IDS.
M|Scor|tx|5. **Pattern recognition.** If the same metric is red three weeks in a row, it is automatically the top issue for IDS.
M|From|When|
M|From|tx|```
M|From|tx|Scorecard rv → Metric is red → Owner drops to Issues List
M|From|tx|→ During IDS, team identifies root cause
M|From|tx|→ Action items assigned (who, what, by when)
M|From|→ Ne|check if action item is complete
M|From|tx|→ Check if metric returned to green
M|From|tx|```
M|From|tx|This weekly cycle ensures no problem goes unaddressed for more than one week. The Scorecard is the early wn sy. The Level 10 meeting is the rp mechanism.
M|Week|it|[ ] Brainstorm 20-30 possible metrics w/ the leadership team
M|Week|it|[ ] Apply the vacation tst to narrow to 5-15
M|Week|it|[ ] Assign one owner per metric
M|Week|it|[ ] Set goals based on 13-week historical average plus 10% stretch
M|Week|it|[ ] cr a simple spreadsheet w/ 13 trailing weeks
M|Week|it|[ ] Commit to reviewing it in the nx Level 10 meeting
M|Week|it|[ ] Remove metrics that are always green (too easy or not meaningful)
M|Week|it|[ ] Replace metrics that nobody understands
M|Week|it|[ ] Adjust goals that were set too hi or too lo
M|Week|it|[ ] Ensure every department has at least one metric on the Scorecard
M|Mont|it|[ ] Everyone can recite the Scorecard metrics from memory
M|Mont|it|[ ] The team looks forward to Scorecard rv (it creates clarity)
M|Mont|it|[ ] Off-track metrics are solved quickly through IDS
M|Mont|it|[ ] New hires are shown the Scorecard in their first week
M|Mont|it|[ ] Department-level scorecards cascade from the company Scorecard